{
    "id": "l1",
    "chapterId": "ch_9",
    "title": "Sync vs Async ⏱️",
    "description": "Waiting for things.",
    "xpReward": 25,
    "estimatedMinutes": 4,
    "section": "Concepts",
    "slides": [
        {
            "id": "s_l1_1",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "One by One 🚶",
            "content": "JavaScript is **Synchronous** by default.\n\nThis means it does one thing at a time, in order.\n\nLine 1 runs, then Line 2, then Line 3."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_2",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l1_1",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "What does synchronous mean?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "Everything happens at once",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "One thing at a time",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "Like a single line at the grocery store."
            }
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_3",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "The Problem 🚧",
            "content": "What if Line 2 takes 5 seconds (like downloading a file)?\n\nIn synchronous code, **the whole page freezes** for 5 seconds!\n\nThis is bad."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_4",
            "type": "text",
            "title": "Asynchronous ⚡",
            "content": "**Asynchronous** code lets JS start a task (like 'Download this') and **move on** to the next line immediately.\n\nIt doesn't wait."
        },
        {
            "id": "s_l1_5",
            "type": "quiz",
            "title": "Quick Check 🧠",
            "content": "",
            "quizData": {
                "id": "q_l1_2",
                "type": "multiple_choice",
                "question": "Why is Async better for slow tasks?",
                "options": [
                    {
                        "id": "opt1",
                        "text": "It keeps the page responsive",
                        "isCorrect": true
                    },
                    {
                        "id": "opt2",
                        "text": "It deletes the task",
                        "isCorrect": false
                    }
                ],
                "explanation": "The user can still click and scroll while the task runs in the background."
            }
        }
    ]
}